Syntax: put <something> {in} <container>

For putting stuff in containers.  The {in} is assumed if it is left out.

In the case of saddlebags or other containers saddled on a horse, use the
terminology "put <object> <horse>" to add objects to the container.

Variations:
put dagger in bag 		: puts one dagger in a bag
put all.bread in bag 		: puts all your bread into a bag
put 9*bread in bag 		: puts 9 of your bread in a bag
put all bag           		: puts entire inventory into a bag
put sword horse			: puts a sword into a container on horse
       
See also: GET, DROP
Related Topics: OBJECT MANIPULATION
